text.tspan: *1: effective Di and ADC precision in [4], because it uses threshold detecting scheme for ADC. Even though its ADC resolution is 7b, the value it reports is 3b (this is a guess. 7b ADC is not possible in this short Tclk Compared to [2] and [3].)
*3: seems in [2] and [3], 8b input will transfer 2 times, but happens in 1 cycle (4b input takes 4.2 ns, while 8b input takes 8.4 ns in [3])
*4: [4] uses delta input, so energy probably is much lower than normal. (seems not affect model fitting.)
*5: sparsity is not reported in paper. This is an assumption.
*6: there are 64 Di, but only 16 are activated in paper.
*7: for aimc3, due to it uses cap-coupling summation method, it's effective Di is 1 when calculating ADC's delay.
result is not accumulated together in IMC macros.
* Agate/Dgate/Cgate: area/delay/capacitance of a NAND2 gate.
* Radc/Badds_out: ADC resolution/output precision of the adder tree
* ICH: the number of input channels
* OCH: the number of output channels
* Bi: precision of input of each input channel
Cost breakdown for a single AIMC macro (cap-coupling based AIMC, because it doesn't have "en" signal compared to charge-sharing based AIMC, so lower energy)

* Agate/Dgate/Cgate: area/delay/capacitance of a NAND2 gate.

* OCH: the number of output channels
* Bi: precision of input of each input channel
